title: Sen. Ernst, who sits on Agriculture Cmte., can’t name price of soybeans
description: Sen. Joni Ernst and her opponent Theresa Greenfield were both asked one of those questions you've just got to know in an Iowa debate. Greenfield nailed it. Ernst’s answer led to one of the most “ouch” debate moments of 2020.

author: Msnbc
title: Sen. David Perdue mocks Kamala Harris’ name at Trump rally
description: Sen. David Perdue mocked Sen. Kamala Harris’ name at a Trump rally in Georgia. He dramatically said to the delight of the crowd, “Kamala? Kamala? Kamala-mala-mala? I don’t know. Whatever.”

author: MSNBC.com
title: We’re in a third Covid spike. Chris Hayes says, ‘There are no more excuses.’
description: “Now we are in the third spike, and there is nothing left to say—other than the President and the Republican Party are willfully getting people killed,” says Chris Hayes.
source.name: MSNBC

author: MSNBC.com
title: Mehdi Hasan on COVID relief: ‘Americans have been abandoned by their government’
description: With 8 million Americans plunged into poverty by the loss of federal aid, Mehdi Hasan, host of Peacock’s ‘The Mehdi Hasan Show,’ and Sheelah Kolhatkar, New Yorker staff writer, describe the failure to pass another relief package as a “betrayal.”
source.name: MSNBC

title: MeToo founder Tarana Burke: ‘Voting is one of the last things we have control of in this country’
description: Tarana Burke, founder of the MeToo movement, says sexual violence survivors are a broad constituency and will be considering Trump’s reputation at the polls.
source.name: MSNBC

title: Velshi: Coronavirus won’t ‘disappear,’ but your vote can help fight it
description: MSNBC’s Ali Velshi says electing a president with a national coronavirus response plan is the first step toward ending the pandemic.

author: MSNBC.com
title: NY Post Hunter Biden story has holes, missing proof journo says
description: The Hunter Biden New York Post stories causing controversy are linked to Rudy Giuliani, co-reported on by an ex-Hannity staffer, have many holes, and provide little proof for key allegations, NPR reporter David Folkenflik tells Tiffany Cross.

author: Marc Ambinder
title: Americans are ready for politics to be boring again
